The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Dalai Lama to inaugurate tie 

Dharamsala: The India-Pakistan cricket series will kick-off on a special note with Tibetan spiritual leader Dalai Lama inaugurating the three-day tour opener here next Thursday. 

The first international match to be played at the newly built stadium of the Himachal Pradesh Cricket Association (HPCA) will also be graced by chief minister V.B. Singh, HPCA president Anurag Thakur said Thursday. 

Doordarshan will telecast the match for which elaborate security arrangements has been made. 

Sale of tickets will begin from Saturday with special concession for school students, Thakur said. (PTI) 




